Alarm and Alarm Systems - installation, servicing or repair
gl_notes: Submit: 1. Installation or monitoring of medical alert systems more than 15% of the insureds total operations 2. Installation or monitoring of alarms at correctional facilities, detention facilities, nursing homes, hospitals banks, federal reserves or transportation facilities 3. Supplemental application required. Prohibited: 1. Chemical, metal and explosive detection devices at transportations facilities, federal buildings or post office mailrooms 2. Fire suppression system installation, service and repair 3. Installation and monitoring of alarms at chemical, fertilizer and petro-chemical facilities 4. Monitoring for home incarceration and pre-trial release 5. Off-shore exposures - gas, oil rigs and ships Credits and Surcharges: 1. Limitation of Liquidated Damages: 15% credit may be applied if the insureds contract contains a limiting provision (often $250) resulting from a system failure. Requirements include: *A copy of the alarm installation/service contract is obtained *The liquidated damages clause is not ever waived by the insured *The clause is on 40% or more of the insureds contracts. 2. A 25% credit may be applied to the liability rates if the Development/ New Residential Exclusion ASIC-GL-0072 is attached. Not applicable to monitoring or retail exposures. 3. (NY only) A 30% credit may be applied to both the Premise and Products/Completed Operations liability rates if the Absolute Employee and Worker Injury and Liability Exclusion (ASIC-GL-0095), is attached, (required if unable to confirm all contractors policies carry full contractual liability with no restrictions for worker injuries or no contracting work is contemplated- do not attach CG 2139 or CG 2426) Required Forms: ASIC-GL-0053, Fungi or Bacteria Exclusion (required if ASIC-GL-0024 is attached to the policy); CG 2116, Exclusion- Designated Professional Services (Indicate: Any and all professional exposures); CG 2154, Exclusion- Designated Operations Covered by a Consolidated (wrap-Up) Insurance Program (Indicate: All operations covered by a consolidated (wrap-up) insurance program); Optional Forms: : ASIC-GL-0072, Development/ New Residential Exclusion; ASIC-GL-0095, (NY only) Absolute Employee and Worker Injury and Liability Exclusion (do not attach CG 2139 or CG 2426); Coverage Options: 1. Electronic Data Liability (CG 0437) is available for limits of: $10,000 = $100 $20,000 = $150 $50,000 = $200 2. Errors and Omissions Coverage (ASIC-GL-0024) is offered at limits equal to the General Liability limit. Charge 10% of the General Liability premium subject to a minimum $100 charge. (do not attach ASIC-GL-0024 with CG 2116) 3. Lost Key Coverage (ASIC-GL-0078) is included at $25,000 /$25,000 limits. 4. Property Damage Extension (ASIC-GL-0076) is included up to $250,000/$500,000 maximum limits, not to exceed GL policy limits.

Swimming/wading pools, hot tubs or spas not in compliance with the Virginia Graeme Baker Pool and Spa Safety Act 7. classname: Restaurants - Bring Your Own Alcohol - with no sale of alcoholic beverages - with table service
prop_notes:
Prohibited: 
Liquor sales in excess of 30%
Credits and Surcharges: 
1. BBQ restaurants, a 25% debit should be applied.
2. Delicatessens, a 15% credit can be applied for delicatessens that do not have a deep fat fryer or appliances that are grease laden or produce grease laden vapors. 
3. Fire suppressant system, a 15% credit can be applied if risk has a wet chemical fire suppression system covering all grease cooking appliances, has a hood, grease removal device and duct systems.  System must be warranted with attachment of CP 0411.
